OL,6,FThe body, responsible for overseeing
OL,7,Fmatch officials, said a thorough
OL,8,Finvestigation had concluded he was "in
OL,9,Fserious breach of the provisions of
OL,10,Fhis employment contract, with his
OL,11,Fposition deemed untenable".
OL,13,F"Supporting David Coote continues to
OL,14,Fbe important to us and we remain
OL,15,Fcommitted to his welfare," PGMOL's
OL,16,Fstatement added.
OL,18,F"David Coote has a right to appeal the
OL,19,Fdecision to terminate his employment."
